The paper deals with algorithms for computing shortest paths in directed planar graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper also discusses the use of dense distance graphs (DDGs) and their applications in various graph problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves computational geometry (cs.CG) since it deals with planar graphs. The use of DDGs also involves graph theory (cs.DM) and graph algorithms (cs.GR). Finally, the paper discusses the development of faster algorithms, which falls under the category of theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
